{"id":225797350,"title":"Nonparametric Bayesian Image Segmentation","authors":["Peter Orbanz","Joachim M Buhmann"],"_abstract":"ABSTRACT Image segmentation algorithms partition the set of pixels of an image into a specific number of different, spatially homogeneous groups. We propose a nonparametric Bayesian model for histogram clustering which automatically determines the number of segments when spatial smoothness constraints on the class assignments are enforced by a Markov Random Field. A Dirichlet process prior controls the level of resolution which corresponds to the number of clusters in data with a unique cluster structure. The resulting posterior is efficiently sampled by a variant of a conjugate-case sampling algorithm for Dirichlet process mixture models. Experimental results are provided for real-world gray value images, synthetic aperture radar images and magnetic resonance imaging data.","cited_in":[{"id":282685393,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/282685393_IJAER"},{"id":230859317,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/230859317_Bayes_procedures_for_adaptive_inference_in_inverse_problems_for_the_white_noise_model"},{"id":264783992,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/264783992_Indian_Sign_Language_Recognition_using_Skin_Colour_Detection"},{"id":237036856,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/237036856_A_spatially-constrained_normalized_Gamma_process_prior"},{"id":278694825,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/278694825_IFIP_Advances_in_Information_and_Communication_Technology"},{"id":221110148,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/221110148_Probabilistic_image_segmentation_with_closedness_constraints"},{"id":224254746,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/224254746_Majorization-minimization_mixture_model_determination_in_image_segmentation"},{"id":228562511,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/228562511_Nonparametric_Bayesian_models_through_probit_stick-breaking_proce